U . S . Plains cattle trade light at $ 70 - feedlots . U . S . Plains feedlot cattle trade was slow at $ 70 . 00 per cwt , mostly steady with Wednesday ' s light activity , feedlot sources said . About 6 , 000 head traded in the Texas Panhandle / western Oklahoma area , sources there said . In Kansas , 500 head had been sold on a carcass basis at $ 113 . 00 per cwt , USDA said . A limited number of cattle sold at $ 71 . 00 Wednesday in Nebraska and Texas , and at $ 114 . 00 on a dressed basis in Nebraska . Packers and cattle owners generally remained at a standoff , with the bulk of owners asking $ 71 . 00 to $ 72 . 00 . 
